<p>on the left of the road, &amp; the two others somewhere on the right but all very near it.</p>
<p>I thought for a second &amp; then told Bill to keep straight on (more by instinct than judgement), &amp; soon we had six in two salvoes just ahead.  The pieces flew all over the place.  We kept on &amp; to our great relief he stopped just before we hurried across the cross roads.</p>
